# Git Rules

## Commit Messages
- Use meaningful commit messages
- Follow conventional commits format
- Reference issue numbers when applicable
- Keep commits focused and atomic
- Use proper commit message formatting

## Branching Strategy
- Follow Git flow branching strategy
- Use feature branches for new features
- Use bugfix branches for bug fixes
- Use release branches for releases
- Use hotfix branches for hotfixes

## Code Review
- Review code before merging
- Use pull requests for code review
- Follow code review checklist
- Address review comments
- Keep pull requests focused

## Version Control
- Use proper versioning
- Tag releases properly
- Keep version history clean
- Use proper merge strategies
- Follow version control best practices

## General Git
- Keep repository clean
- Use proper .gitignore
- Use proper .gitattributes
- Use proper Git hooks

